The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 08 December is 303,619 (34,993.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 03 December, there were 468 new confirmed cases (53.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 26 November, there were 335 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 40% (133 extra cases).
